"It is no exaggeration to say that every woman who arrives here has experienced sexual violence on the run", says Bahr.
"Men flee wars because of political persecution, because of threats of torture or death, or because their families send them to Europe as hope", she says.
For women, other reasons outweigh the escape: "Many sneak away because they see no other way out".
