What causes sleep disorders?
The causes of sleep disorders are complex.
This may be due to organic, psychological, or behavioral factors, as well as medications.
Often, the sleep disorder is a manifestation of another illness.
"Waking up too early is especially common in depression", says Weeß.
And it may be that different factors are causing each other.
For example, someone with a herniated disc may lie unwell, wake up every two to three hours, and may begin to dwell on everyday problems and worries, explains Weiss.
This creates tension, and sleep is no longer possible.
