Thuringia: Zeiss Meditec approaches billion in sales
A high demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted Carl Zeiss Meditec's sales.
In the first nine months of the financial year, which began in October, the Group's turnover increased by 6.7 percent to EUR 798.6 million, the listed company said on Friday in Jena.
The Asian business grew disproportionately by 17.1 per cent.
Profit before interest and taxes increased from EUR 89.5 million to EUR 110.5 million according to the interim balance sheet.
The Jena medical technology group wants to exceed the turnover mark of one billion euros this financial year, the management confirmed.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures equipment for medical practices and clinics.
The company, which belongs to the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs almost 3000 people.
